  "article": {
    "published_at": "2026-04-03T09:35:27.000000Z",
    "id": 2040000216456143000,
    "id_str": "2040000216456143002",
    "title": "8 Claude Code Hooks That Automate What You Keep Forgetting ",
    "preview_text": "Have you ever told Claude Code to do something and it just didn't?\nYou said format the code - It didn't. You said don't touch that file - It did. \nYou said run tests before finishing - It forgot.",
    "cover_url": "https://pbs.twimg.com/media/HE-H4DhXwAAV4XA.jpg",
    "content_state": {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "7oqic",
          "text": "Have you ever told Claude Code to do something and it just didn't?",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "4a2j3",
          "text": "You said format the code - It didn't. You said don't touch that file - It did. ",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "1kg3",
          "text": "You said run tests before finishing - It forgot.",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [
            {
              "length": 41,
              "offset": 0,
              "style": "Bold"
            }
          ],
          "key": "3c33",
          "text": "That's because CLAUDE.md is a suggestion.",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "46o39",
          "text": " Claude reads it and follows it about 80% of the time. Hooks are different. They're automatic actions that fire every time Claude edits a file, runs a command, or finishes a task.",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [
            {
              "key": 0,
              "length": 1,
              "offset": 110
            }
          ],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "5i2l",
          "text": "Below I will share 8 personal hooks you can copy straight into your settings.json and never think about again 👇",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": {
            "urls": [
              {
                "fromIndex": 83,
                "text": "https://t.me/zodchixquant",
                "toIndex": 108
              }
            ]
          },
          "entityRanges": [
            {
              "key": 1,
              "length": 1,
              "offset": 108
            }
          ],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [
            {
              "length": 25,
              "offset": 83,
              "style": "Bold"
            }
          ],
          "key": "6p2t",
          "text": "Before we dive in, I share daily notes on AI & vibe coding in my Telegram channel: https://t.me/zodchixquant🧠",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [
            {
              "key": 2,
              "length": 1,
              "offset": 0
            }
          ],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "d6j5q",
          "text": " ",
          "type": "atomic"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "7i1ll",
          "text": "How hooks work (30-second version)\n\nWhat are hooks?",
          "type": "header-two"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "bv5vh",
          "text": "Hooks are automatic actions that run every time Claude Code does something, like editing a file or running a command. ",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "7poom",
          "text": "You set them up once and they work in the background without you thinking about it.",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "393m9",
          "text": "The two you'll use most:",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [
            {
              "length": 10,
              "offset": 0,
              "style": "Bold"
            }
          ],
          "key": "cnf7s",
          "text": "PreToolUse runs before Claude does something. You can inspect the action and block it by returning exit code 2. Think of it as a bouncer.",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [
            {
              "length": 11,
              "offset": 0,
              "style": "Bold"
            }
          ],
          "key": "2sij2",
          "text": "PostToolUse runs after Claude does something. You can run cleanup, formatting, tests, or logging. Think of it as quality control on the assembly line.",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [
            {
              "key": 3,
              "length": 1,
              "offset": 0
            }
          ],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "1thaj",
          "text": " ",
          "type": "atomic"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [
            {
              "length": 21,
              "offset": 22,
              "style": "Bold"
            }
          ],
          "key": "btrpf",
          "text": "You configure them in .claude/settings.json in your project root. That file gets committed to git, so your whole team gets the same hooks automatically.",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": {
            "urls": [
              {
                "fromIndex": 20,
                "text": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/hooks",
                "toIndex": 57
              }
            ]
          },
          "entityRanges": [
            {
              "key": 4,
              "length": 37,
              "offset": 20
            }
          ],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "dmm6d",
          "text": "Full documentation: https://code.claude.com/docs/en/hooks",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [
            {
              "key": 5,
              "length": 1,
              "offset": 0
            }
          ],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "bush3",
          "text": " ",
          "type": "atomic"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "9q38c",
          "text": "1. Auto-format every file Claude touches",
          "type": "header-two"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [
            {
              "length": 12,
              "offset": 0,
              "style": "Bold"
            }
          ],
          "key": "38ep2",
          "text": "The problem: Claude writes correct code that breaks your formatting rules. You add \"always run Prettier\" to CLAUDE.md and it works most of the time, but not always.",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [
            {
              "length": 9,
              "offset": 0,
              "style": "Bold"
            }
          ],
          "key": "e1elg",
          "text": "The hook: Prettier runs automatically after every file write or edit.",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [
            {
              "key": 6,
              "length": 1,
              "offset": 0
            }
          ],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "f208",
          "text": " ",
          "type": "atomic"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [
            {
              "length": 20,
              "offset": 5,
              "style": "Bold"
            },
            {
              "length": 5,
              "offset": 58,
              "style": "Bold"
            },
            {
              "length": 5,
              "offset": 76,
              "style": "Bold"
            },
            {
              "length": 7,
              "offset": 90,
              "style": "Bold"
            }
          ],
          "key": "9pt7u",
          "text": "Swap npx prettier --write for whatever formatter you use: black for Python, gofmt for Go, rustfmt for Rust. The pattern is the same.",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "7gtbt",
          "text": "This was the first hook I set up and honestly it should be the default for every project. No more \"Claude forgot to format\" commits.",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [
            {
              "length": 27,
              "offset": 0,
              "style": "Bold"
            }
          ],
          "key": "b7lqi",
          "text": "2. Block dangerous commands",
          "type": "header-two"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [
            {
              "length": 12,
              "offset": 0,
              "style": "Bold"
            }
          ],
          "key": "bnmho",
          "text": "The problem: Claude is powerful enough to run rm -rf, git reset --hard, DROP TABLE, or curl to random URLs. It probably won't, but \"probably\" isn't good enough when it's your production database.",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [
            {
              "length": 9,
              "offset": 0,
              "style": "Bold"
            }
          ],
          "key": "69l9u",
          "text": "The hook: Block destructive commands before they execute.",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "ar2ag",
          "text": "Create .claude/hooks/block-dangerous.sh:",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [
            {
              "key": 7,
              "length": 1,
              "offset": 0
            }
          ],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "6jn82",
          "text": " ",
          "type": "atomic"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "6ae9s",
          "text": "Then add to your settings.json:",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [
            {
              "key": 8,
              "length": 1,
              "offset": 0
            }
          ],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "ekkhj",
          "text": " ",
          "type": "atomic"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "6c435",
          "text": "Exit code 2 is the key. It blocks the action and sends your error message back to Claude so it can try a safer approach. Exit code 0 means \"go ahead.\" Anything else logs a warning but doesn't block.",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "c22qn",
          "text": "3. Protect sensitive files from edits",
          "type": "header-two"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [
            {
              "length": 12,
              "offset": 0,
              "style": "Bold"
            },
            {
              "length": 24,
              "offset": 77,
              "style": "Bold"
            }
          ],
          "key": "3e8us",
          "text": "The problem: Claude can read and edit any file in your project. That includes .env, package-lock.json, config files, and anything else you'd rather it didn't touch.",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [
            {
              "length": 9,
              "offset": 0,
              "style": "Bold"
            }
          ],
          "key": "2ndlt",
          "text": "The hook: Block edits to files that should be off-limits.",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [
            {
              "length": 31,
              "offset": 7,
              "style": "Bold"
            }
          ],
          "key": "9k4jl",
          "text": "Create .claude/hooks/protect-files.sh:",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [
            {
              "key": 9,
              "length": 1,
              "offset": 0
            }
          ],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "1hntj",
          "text": " ",
          "type": "atomic"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [
            {
              "key": 10,
              "length": 1,
              "offset": 0
            }
          ],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "c71lg",
          "text": " ",
          "type": "atomic"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "1260a",
          "text": "",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "ajis3",
          "text": "4. Run tests after every edit",
          "type": "header-two"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [
            {
              "length": 12,
              "offset": 0,
              "style": "Bold"
            }
          ],
          "key": "cl1l8",
          "text": "The problem: Claude makes a change, says \"done,\" and you discover the tests are broken 20 minutes later when you try to commit.",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [
            {
              "length": 9,
              "offset": 0,
              "style": "Bold"
            }
          ],
          "key": "1bk02",
          "text": "The hook: Run your test suite automatically after every code change. If tests fail, Claude sees the failure and can fix it immediately.",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [
            {
              "key": 11,
              "length": 1,
              "offset": 0
            }
          ],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "e9bs8",
          "text": " ",
          "type": "atomic"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [
            {
              "length": 8,
              "offset": 4,
              "style": "Bold"
            }
          ],
          "key": "25q9t",
          "text": "The tail -5 keeps the output short so it doesn't flood Claude's context. You want Claude to see \"3 tests failed\" not the full 200-line test output.",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "ct0uh",
          "text": "Boris Cherny, the creator of Claude Code, says giving Claude a feedback loop like this improves output quality by 2-3x. Instead of writing code and hoping it works, Claude writes code, sees the test results, and fixes failures on its own.",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "91aih",
          "text": "5. Require passing tests before creating a PR",
          "type": "header-two"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [
            {
              "length": 12,
              "offset": 0,
              "style": "Bold"
            }
          ],
          "key": "9sijd",
          "text": "The problem: Claude finishes a feature and immediately creates a PR. Tests are failing. Your reviewer sees red CI and sends it back.",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [
            {
              "length": 9,
              "offset": 0,
              "style": "Bold"
            }
          ],
          "key": "562em",
          "text": "The hook: Block PR creation unless all tests pass.",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [
            {
              "length": 38,
              "offset": 7,
              "style": "Bold"
            }
          ],
          "key": "4d9oi",
          "text": "Create .claude/hooks/require-tests-for-pr.sh:",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [
            {
              "key": 12,
              "length": 1,
              "offset": 0
            }
          ],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "bpdic",
          "text": " ",
          "type": "atomic"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [
            {
              "key": 13,
              "length": 1,
              "offset": 0
            }
          ],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "ba0kv",
          "text": " ",
          "type": "atomic"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "d2dmh",
          "text": "This is a hard gate. No green tests, no PR. Claude will fix the failures first because exit code 2 tells it the action was blocked and why.",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "3vj6p",
          "text": "6. Auto-lint and report errors",
          "type": "header-two"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [
            {
              "length": 12,
              "offset": 0,
              "style": "Bold"
            }
          ],
          "key": "cm9hq",
          "text": "The problem: Claude writes code that works but violates your ESLint rules, style guide, or type checks. You catch it during review and send it back.",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [
            {
              "length": 9,
              "offset": 0,
              "style": "Bold"
            }
          ],
          "key": "99jpf",
          "text": "The hook: Lint after every edit. If lint fails, Claude sees the errors and fixes them before you ever look at the code.",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [
            {
              "key": 14,
              "length": 1,
              "offset": 0
            }
          ],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "f48kf",
          "text": " ",
          "type": "atomic"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "cfkek",
          "text": "You can chain this with the auto-format hook from #1. Prettier runs first, then ESLint. By the time you see the code, it's formatted and lint-clean.",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "bd418",
          "text": "7. Log every command Claude runs",
          "type": "header-two"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [
            {
              "length": 12,
              "offset": 0,
              "style": "Bold"
            }
          ],
          "key": "bhpg6",
          "text": "The problem: Claude runs a lot of shell commands during a session. If something goes wrong, you want to know exactly what it did and when.",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [
            {
              "length": 9,
              "offset": 0,
              "style": "Bold"
            }
          ],
          "key": "1jfqk",
          "text": "The hook: Append every Bash command to a log file with timestamps.",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [
            {
              "length": 30,
              "offset": 7,
              "style": "Bold"
            }
          ],
          "key": "cfg1e",
          "text": "Create .claude/hooks/log-commands.sh:",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [
            {
              "key": 15,
              "length": 1,
              "offset": 0
            }
          ],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "eg6bp",
          "text": " ",
          "type": "atomic"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [
            {
              "key": 16,
              "length": 1,
              "offset": 0
            }
          ],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "69hok",
          "text": " ",
          "type": "atomic"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [
            {
              "length": 23,
              "offset": 72,
              "style": "Bold"
            },
            {
              "length": 9,
              "offset": 105,
              "style": "Bold"
            }
          ],
          "key": "978pc",
          "text": "Now you have a timestamped audit trail of every command Claude ran. Add .claude/command-log.txt to your .gitignore so it doesn't pollute your repo.",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "5c5ft",
          "text": "This is especially useful for debugging: if Claude broke something three sessions ago, you can look at the log and find exactly when and what it ran.",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "bsfrn",
          "text": "8. Auto-commit after each completed task",
          "type": "header-two"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [
            {
              "length": 12,
              "offset": 0,
              "style": "Bold"
            }
          ],
          "key": "cn207",
          "text": "The problem: Claude finishes a task and you forget to commit. Then it starts another task and now you have two unrelated changes mixed together in one commit.",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [
            {
              "length": 9,
              "offset": 0,
              "style": "Bold"
            }
          ],
          "key": "dl91",
          "text": "The hook: Automatically commit all changes when Claude stops working on a task.",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [
            {
              "length": 30,
              "offset": 6,
              "style": "Bold"
            }
          ],
          "key": "s6i1",
          "text": "Create .claude/hooks/auto-commit.sh:",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [
            {
              "key": 17,
              "length": 1,
              "offset": 0
            }
          ],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "1j11f",
          "text": " ",
          "type": "atomic"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [
            {
              "key": 18,
              "length": 1,
              "offset": 0
            }
          ],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "5f130",
          "text": " ",
          "type": "atomic"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "fjcim",
          "text": "Every time Claude finishes a response, changes get committed automatically. Your git history stays clean with atomic commits per task instead of one massive \"Claude changes\" blob at the end of the day.",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [
            {
              "length": 24,
              "offset": 18,
              "style": "Bold"
            }
          ],
          "key": "a786p",
          "text": "Combine this with claude -w feature-branch (worktrees) and you get isolated, auto-committed feature branches for every task.",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "ekdb1",
          "text": "The complete settings.json",
          "type": "header-two"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "11m9n",
          "text": "Here's everything combined into one file you can copy-paste:",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "b2f1b",
          "text": "Screenshot-friendly:",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [
            {
              "key": 19,
              "length": 1,
              "offset": 0
            }
          ],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "curbd",
          "text": " ",
          "type": "atomic"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [
            {
              "length": 21,
              "offset": 20,
              "style": "Bold"
            },
            {
              "length": 15,
              "offset": 70,
              "style": "Bold"
            },
            {
              "length": 27,
              "offset": 112,
              "style": "Bold"
            }
          ],
          "key": "4uqg4",
          "text": "Copy this file into .claude/settings.json, create the hook scripts in .claude/hooks/, make them executable with chmod +x .claude/hooks/*.sh, and commit everything to git. Your whole team gets the same safety nets automatically.",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [
            {
              "key": 20,
              "length": 1,
              "offset": 0
            }
          ],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "12gil",
          "text": " ",
          "type": "atomic"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "7rb8i",
          "text": "The difference between a good Claude Code setup and a great one isn't the model or the prompts. It's the hooks. ",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "404sd",
          "text": "They're the part that runs when you're not paying attention, catching the mistakes you'd otherwise find during code review or worse, in production.",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "6o1n2",
          "text": "Set up hook #1 (auto-format) and #2 (block dangerous commands) today. That alone will save you from the most common Claude Code mistakes. Add the rest as you need them.",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": {
            "urls": [
              {
                "fromIndex": 76,
                "text": "https://t.me/zodchixquant",
                "toIndex": 101
              }
            ]
          },
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [
            {
              "length": 25,
              "offset": 76,
              "style": "Bold"
            }
          ],
          "key": "cs1fv",
          "text": "I share daily notes on AI, finance, and vibe coding in my Telegram channel: https://t.me/zodchixquant",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [
            {
              "key": 21,
              "length": 2,
              "offset": 19
            }
          ],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "cv678",
          "text": "Thanks for reading 🙏🏼",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
